         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:meunier2013"/><citedRange>165</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">To (our) teacher, the <hi>Aśari</hi>. The whole <hi>saṃgha</hi> living in Samatatir makes greetings (to you).</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a10"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Because of this extreme situation, in the refuge in <hi>Śaṅke</hi> ('s place), he acts... unfriendly against us.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a11 #a12"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Now, the teacher (= the addressee) will please consider the way for us: how the monastery will not (lose?) estate again, (so that) the well-being of (my) <hi>saṃgha</hi> will not be spoilt. In the 1st regnal year, in the 12th month.</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">May the ācārya now think about an approach [lit. way] for us, so that the monastery will not (lose estate?)334 for a second time, and the proper situation of the community will not be terminated.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>324</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a13"><seg><seg type="prim_transl"><hi>Wiryamitre</hi> the <hi>Saṅkästere wi</hi></seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a14"><seg><seg type="prim_transl"><hi>Wäryasene</hi> the <hi>Stere w<hi rend="subscript">ry</hi></hi></seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a15"><seg><seg type="prim_transl"><hi>Jñānasene</hi> the <hi>Stere ñ<hi rend="subscript">ā</hi></hi> <hi>Mokṣacandre</hi> the <hi>Praskāre m<hi rend="subscript">o</hi></hi></seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a16"><seg><seg type="prim_transl"><hi>Āryatewe</hi> the [Stere] <hi>ā</hi></seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2 #a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Oh lord! Because of (your) divine-like wisdom, you might already know how my <hi>Samantatir</hi> Monastery have been miserable and detestable for years.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3 #a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Now, because of the effort of the Elders <hi>Āryatewe</hi> (and) <hi>Jñānasene</hi>, the monastery ... was re-established. The situation of the <hi>saṃgha</hi> is (now) proper, (and) we are attached to the good behavior (Skt. <hi>kuśalapakṣa-</hi>).</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:adams2012"/><citedRange>9</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4 #a5 #a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Oh lord! Concerning the four thousand (coins) as the previous debt owed by <hi>Puttisene</hi> with (our?) signature, the man from whom (the coins) were given did not keep contact with him. (Because) the man has been ... afar.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:ching2010"/><citedRange>137</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Now, he (<hi>Puttisene</hi>?) has undertaken the official labor services (to deliver) letters from <hi>Śiṅku(n)</hi>.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6 #a7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:adams2012"/><citedRange>9</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">In a manner deprived of (all) decency, he (= the creditor?) humiliates the <hi>saṃgha</hi> again (and) again.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a7 #a8"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Oh lord! (How) <hi>Puttisene</hi> had watched (over) this monastery, he (= the creditor?) seized (lit. 'robbed') in the same way.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a8"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">So far is (our) account of the (accident).</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a8 #a9"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">What he has taken, he must give (back) to us. What we owe to him, we will give it to him.</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">If he gives back to me what he has carried off, we [will] give back to him what we owe.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>315</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a9 #a10"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Oh lord! What he has seized (lit. 'robbed'), he does not think (about its value). It is imposed on me as the *<hi>ṣorye</hi>-debt because of the violation (of contract?).</seg></seg></choice></p>
