               <item n="file_name_old">pages/manuscript/PK_DA/pkda507_32.txt</item>
               <item n="m_translation_old">a1 To (our) teacher, the &lt;i&gt;Aśari&lt;/i&gt;. The whole &lt;i&gt;saṃgha&lt;/i&gt; living in Samatatir makes greetings (to you).
a2-3 Oh lord! Because of (your) divine-like wisdom, you might already know how my &lt;i&gt;Samantatir&lt;/i&gt; Monastery have been miserable and detestable for years.
a3-4 Now, because of the effort of the Elders &lt;i&gt;Āryatewe&lt;/i&gt; (and) &lt;i&gt;Jñānasene&lt;/i&gt;, the monastery ... was re-established. The situation of the &lt;i&gt;saṃgha&lt;/i&gt; is (now) proper, (and) we are attached to the good behavior (Skt. &lt;i&gt;kuśalapakṣa-&lt;/i&gt;).
a4-6 Oh lord! Concerning the four thousand (coins) as the previous debt owed by &lt;i&gt;Puttisene&lt;/i&gt; with (our?) signature, the man from whom (the coins) were given did not keep contact with him. (Because) the man has been ... afar.
a6 Now, he (&lt;i&gt;Puttisene&lt;/i&gt;?) has undertaken the official labor services (to deliver) letters from &lt;i&gt;Śiṅku(n)&lt;/i&gt;.
a6-7 In a manner deprived of (all) decency, he (= the creditor?) humiliates the &lt;i&gt;saṃgha&lt;/i&gt; again (and) again.
a7-8 Oh lord! (How) &lt;i&gt;Puttisene&lt;/i&gt; had watched (over) this monastery, he (= the creditor?) seized (lit. 'robbed') in the same way.
a8 So far is (our) account of the (accident).
a8-9 What he has taken, he must give (back) to us. What we owe to him, we will give it to him.
a9-10 Oh lord! What he has seized (lit. 'robbed'), he does not think (about its value). It is imposed on me as the *&lt;i&gt;ṣorye&lt;/i&gt;-debt because of the violation (of contract?).
a10 Because of this extreme situation, in the refuge in &lt;i&gt;Śaṅke&lt;/i&gt; ('s place), he acts... unfriendly against us.
a11-12 Now, the teacher (= the addressee) will please consider the way for us: how the monastery will not (lose?) estate again, (so that) the well-being of (my) &lt;i&gt;saṃgha&lt;/i&gt; will not be spoilt. In the 1st regnal year, in the 12th month.
a13 &lt;i&gt;Wiryamitre&lt;/i&gt; the &lt;i&gt;Saṅkästere wi&lt;/i&gt;
a14 &lt;i&gt;Wäryasene&lt;/i&gt; the &lt;i&gt;Stere w&lt;sub&gt;ry&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
a15 &lt;i&gt;Jñānasene&lt;/i&gt; the &lt;i&gt;Stere ñ&lt;sub&gt;ā&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;Mokṣacandre&lt;/i&gt; the &lt;i&gt;Praskāre m&lt;sub&gt;o&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
a16 &lt;i&gt;Āryatewe&lt;/i&gt; the [Stere] &lt;i&gt;ā&lt;/i&gt;</item>
